¨©ÞU<?php exit; ?>a:6:{s:10:"last_error";s:0:"";s:10:"last_query";s:183:"SELECT   wp_posts.* FROM wp_posts  WHERE 1=1  AND wp_posts.post_name = 'using-markerswithlabel-class-on-google-maps' AND wp_posts.post_type = 'post'  ORDER BY wp_posts.post_date DESC ";s:11:"last_result";a:1:{i:0;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"315";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2015-07-17 07:44:30";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2015-07-17 02:14:30";s:12:"post_content";s:3483:"<p>We have already seen custom overlays, we had full freedom to customize it the way we want it. Now there are some good people working hard to make things simple and application specific. If you want some markers which has image and a text below. Go and use markerswithlabel class.</p>
<p>I am giving the code for class below or you can also download it from Download code option.</p>
<p><span>[button colour="orange" type="roundedarrow" size="large" link="http://demo.webtutplus.com/markerwithlabel.php" target="_blank"]Try it![/button]Â [button colour="orange" type="roundedarrow" size="large" link="http://demo.webtutplus.com/markerwithlabel.zip" target="_blank"]Download Code[/button]</span></p>
<pre class="prettyprint lang-javascript"><!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
 <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
 
 <style type="text/css">
   .labels {
     color: red;
     background-color: white;
     font-family: "Lucida Grande", "Arial", sans-serif;
     font-size: 10px;
     font-weight: bold;
     text-align: center;
     width: 100px;
     border: 1px solid black;
     white-space: nowrap;
   }
 </style>
 <script type="text/javascript" src="http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?v=3&sensor=false"></script>
 <script type="text/javascript" src="./markerwithlabelashish.js"></script>
 <script type="text/javascript">
   function initMap() {
     var latLng = new google.maps.LatLng(49.47805, -123.84716);
     var homeLatLng = new google.maps.LatLng(49.47805, -123.84716);

     var map = new google.maps.Map(document.getElementById('map_canvas'), {
       zoom: 12,
       center: latLng,
       mapTypeId: google.maps.MapTypeId.ROADMAP
     });

     var marker1 = new MarkerWithLabel({
       position: homeLatLng,
       title : 'Some Title',
       Icon : 'img/bike.png',
       draggable: true,
       raiseOnDrag: true,
       map: map,
       labelContent: "Some Bike",
       labelAnchor: new google.maps.Point(22, 0),
       labelClass: "labels", // the CSS class for the label
       labelStyle: {opacity: 0.5},
     });
   }
 </script>
</head>
<body onload="initMap()">

 <div id="map_canvas" style="height: 400px; width: 100%;"></div>
 
</body>
</html></pre>
<p>Didn't you notice Its pretty simple. Simple than how we used custom overlays on google maps. But it dose depend on the requirement. If you need such custom overlays then I recommend you to use this class.</p>
<p><span style="color: #99cc00;">Understanding the code :</span></p>
<p><strong>labelContent: "Some Bike"</strong></p>
<p>This is the content you would like to put as label under the image.</p>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<p><strong>labelAnchor: new google.maps.Point(22, 0)</strong></p>
<p>Anchor location for label with respect to the marker, try changing the value here and you will get it soon.</p>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<p><strong>labelClass: "labels"</strong></p>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<p>If you have observed the code carefully, above all I have defined a labels class and properties for the class, just check those out. This is how your label is going to be displayed.Â </p>
<p><strong>labelStyle: {opacity: 0.5}</strong></p>
<p>You know this , opacity of the object over the map.</p>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Class File :</span></p>
<p>No. i am not giving it here. Its loo long, just download the zip file and the class file is already there.Â </p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
